      "text": "Previous slide Next slide 1 of 21 View All Skip Ad \nThe best of British and Indian culture has been celebrated by the Queen at a glittering Buckingham Palace reception attended by the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge. Guests from the worlds of sport, fashion, show-business and the arts were invited to the event held to launch the UK-India Year of Culture 2017, marking the close ties between the two nations. \nA peacock design was projected on to the front of Buckingham Palace. The peacock is the national bird of India. The projection has been designed by Studio Carrom, the Bangalore and London-based design studio, who have created the eye-catching display. SWNS.com",
