      "title": "Mumbai ahead of Washington, Toronto in super-rich population list; home to 1340 ultra HNIs",
      "text": "Mumbai ahead of Washington, Toronto in super-rich population list; home to 1340 ultra HNIs By Zee Media Bureau | Last Updated: Wednesday, March 1, 2017 - 15:41 0 Follow @ZeeNews \nMumbai: India's financial capital Mumbai has ranked 21st in the 'City Wealth Index' list prepared by Real estate agency Knight Frank tracking super-rich population in 125 cities across 89 countries. \nThe Knight Frank Wealth Report 2017 has placed Mumbai ahead of Toronto, Washington DC and Moscow while Delhi ranks at number 35. \nCheck out list of India's richest cities and their total wealth \nThe national capital is ahead of Bangkok, Seattle and Jakarta. \nThe number of ultrahigh net worth individuals (UHNWI) in India has increased by 290 percent during the last decade. India houses 2 percent of the world's millionaires (13.6 million) and 5 percent of world's billionaires (2,024). \nMumbai is home to 1340 UHNWIs followed by Delhi (680), Kolkata (280) and Hyderabad (260). \nMeanwhile cities like Pune (18%), Hyderabad and Bangalore (both at 15%) saw rise in UHNWIs as compared to 2015. \nIn the 'future wealth' category, Mumbai ranks 11 ahead of Chicago, Sydney, Paris, Seoul and Dubai. \nIn terms of most expensive prime residential Mumbai ranks 15, three notches above from that of last year's performance. Mumbai is ahead of Istanbul, Melbourne and Dubai. First Published: Wednesday, March 1, 2017 - 15:18",
