      "title": "The advantages of working in a co-working space - YourStory.com",
      "text": "Flipboard \nCo-working can be best defined as the practice of sharing an office with strangers rather than working by oneself at home. Working in a co-working space has become the latest trend owing to its many advantages. It is an innovative alternative to traditional cubicles and make-shift setups like a coffee shop. This type of working has been proven to be beneficial for running a business and maintaining a professional career. It not only helps you quickly and efficiently network but also helps your business grow exponentially with the new contacts you make. If you’re still wondering why to invest in a co-working space, here are some pointers for you. \nImage : shutterstock Easy on the pocket \nSeveral co-working spaces offer an economical and affordable rent , especially in comparison to hiring an entire corporate office space. Most won't even get you to sign a long-term contract. Depending on your requirements, you'll be able to find places that offer daily rates or even month-long contracts. This will ensure that you aren't committing to a place until and unless you're absolutely sure about it. Most co-working spaces offer access to basic necessities as well. So you won't have to invest in fax machines and printers at least at the beginning of your business. Make new connections \nNo matter what business you're running, who you know is just as important as what you know. Apart from being affordable, one of the main advantages of working at a co-working space is that everyone who walks through the door is a professional in their own right and will enrich you either personally or professionally with their personality and skill set. Working from home needs a certain amount of motivation to get out of bed, switch on the laptop, and accomplish your day's tasks. On the other hand, at a co-working space you'll be surrounded by similar minded people who will be just as passionate and goal-driven as you are, and this will push you to be a better version of yourself. Easy accessibility to talent \nCo-working spaces attract a wide variety of talent from various industries and different fields. If you're stuck with a persistent problem, you can be sure that the person sitting next to you will have a solution to your problem. Take advantage of the fact that you can trade and share skills with those around you as this will help you gain a lot of potential clients and customers in the process. You can also scout for and hire individuals, either on a project basis or long term, to help you out with certain aspects of your business. With the best of talent available at an arm's distance, one would be a fool to not make use of it. \nCo-working is a resourceful way to increase the positive effects of a work place, while mitigating the negative effects of working at home or in a public space. There is a constant feeling of community and bonhomie in a shared work place which makes this concept of corporate functioning an innovative one. Calling all Bangalore startups! Here is a chance to learn tricks of the trade and interact with the the ones who’ve made it big, or to interact with people like you. Learn everything that your growth story needs! Register now! Limited seats apply! 0 ",
